README

Instructions:
1. Place Hex.cpp and Makefile into the same folder in UNIX timeshare.
2. Type "make" (without quotation marks) into UNIX terminal.
3. Type "Hex" (without quotation marks) into UNIX terminal to execute program.

This program is a C++ implementation of the Hex board game with 2 players.
It runs every possible move for the AI to make 1000 times each. It then chooses the move with the most amount
of wins and makes that move.
It uses a depth first search algorithm to determine the winner.
Multithreading has been implemented and is compile with the "-lpthread" flag in the Makefile.
